{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000002:issue_created:sase-5l.1","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:09:50Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.1","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.1","title":"doctor: add llm.auth offline provider auth-evidence check","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:09:50Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:09:50Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add a default, offline-only llm.auth diagnostic to sase doctor (register in src/sase/doctor/runner.py). OK when the selected provider CLI is present and local credential evidence or a relevant API-key env var exists; WARN when the CLI is present but no local auth evidence is found; SKIP when llm.default already reports the CLI missing. Drive it from provider-declared credential-path and API-key-env metadata (add registry/hook metadata; reuse _PROVIDER_SETUP_HINTS), never an if-provider ladder. Keep auth_verified false unless a provider-owned bounded status command can verify without an LLM call, quota use, or interactive login. Add focused tests. See research section 1 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000003:issue_created:sase-5l.2","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:10:18Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.2","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.2","title":"doctor: add install.management uv-tool readiness check","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:10:18Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:10:18Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add a default install.management (or runtime.install_management) diagnostic reusing the existing pure detector in src/sase/uv_tool/detect.py. OK for a confirmed uv-tool install; WARN (never ERROR) for pip, pipx, dev venv, missing uv, wrong prefix, or missing uv-receipt.toml. Surface data: uv_path, tool_dir, sys_prefix, receipt_path, reason, managed. Reveals sase update, plugin management, Admin Center update flows, and chat-driven install/update workers may be unavailable from this environment. Add tests. See research section 2 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000004:issue_created:sase-5l.3","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:10:43Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.3","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.3","title":"doctor: add resources.disk_free check","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:10:43Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:10:43Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add a default resources.disk_free diagnostic in a new resources check group. ERROR when the workspace root has under ~1 GB free; WARN under ~3 GB; OK otherwise. Include sase_home as a secondary path. Next steps: free space or run sase workspace cleanup; note live workspaces can consume hundreds of MB to over 1 GB after checkout and .venv creation. Rationale: numbered workspaces are real git clones (_ensure_git_clone_at raises on failure), so a full disk hard-fails agent launch even though state.paths reports writable. Add tests. See research section 3 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000005:issue_created:sase-5l.4","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:11:00Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.4","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.4","title":"doctor: add tools.editor shared editor resolver and check","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:11:00Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:11:00Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Create one shared editor resolver and reuse it from doctor and the editor call sites (src/sase/workflows/commit/editor_utils.py, src/sase/main/query_handler/_editor.py, src/sase/ace/tui/actions/agent_workflow/_editor.py). Add a default tools.editor check: OK when VISUAL/EDITOR or nvim/vim resolves; WARN when the selected command head is missing or only an unverified shell command was configured. Support commands like code --wait as valid. Add tests. See research section 4 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000006:issue_created:sase-5l.5","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:11:24Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.5","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.5","title":"doctor: promote tools.tmux and tools.clipboard to default","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:11:24Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:11:24Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Promote tmux and clipboard checks from deep-only to default (part of splitting tools.optional into a default core-UX set and a deep artifact/rendering set). tools.tmux: WARN (not ERROR) if missing; sase ace --tmux hard-exits code 2 and tmux enables workspace windows, inline artifact panes, and artifact zoom; agents themselves do not need tmux. tools.clipboard: reuse clipboard_available() from src/sase/core/clipboard.py with platform-aware next steps (wl-clipboard, xclip, xsel, or pbcopy). Keep niche artifact/rendering tools deep. Add tests. See research section 5 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000007:issue_created:sase-5l.6","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:11:52Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.6","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.6","title":"doctor: add integrations.mobile_push_config coherence check","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:11:52Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:11:52Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add a default integrations.mobile_push_config check that skips when push is disabled. SKIP when push disabled; OK for push_provider test, fcm_dry_run, or a complete FCM config; ERROR when fcm is selected but fcm_project_id or a credential source (service-account path or credential-env) is missing. Rationale: launch prep in src/sase/integrations/mobile_gateway.py appends FCM flags only when values are non-empty, so incoherent config passes through silently. Do NOT add any MCP diagnostic (MCP is not implemented in this repo). Add tests. See research section 6 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000008:issue_created:sase-5l.7","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:12:18Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.7","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.7","title":"doctor: add runtime.node conditional setup check","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:12:18Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:12:18Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add a default runtime.node check that WARNs only when node/npm is missing AND an npm-distributed provider (claude, codex, qwen use npm install -g per src/sase/doctor/checks_providers.py) is registered but its CLI is not found; otherwise SKIP or OK. Node is not a universal SASE requirement, so avoid unconditional warnings. Add tests. See research section 7 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000009:issue_created:sase-5l.8","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:13:05Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.8","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.8","title":"doctor: surface tools.fzf in top-level doctor","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:13:05Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:13:05Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add a tools.fzf check to sase doctor (default if top-level doctor is first-run readiness, else deep) so it is not only in sase prompt doctor. WARN when missing. fzf gates prompt pickers and editor prompt history (the editor path in src/sase/main/query_handler/_editor.py prints an error when fzf is missing). Add tests. See research section 8 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000010:issue_created:sase-5l.9","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:13:34Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.9","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.9","title":"doctor: add integrations.mobile_gateway_binary deep check","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:13:34Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:13:34Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add a deep integrations.mobile_gateway_binary check. SKIP when mobile is unused; WARN when the mobile gateway is configured but no sase_gateway command resolves (mirror the gateway binary resolver in src/sase/integrations/mobile_gateway.py read-only). Add tests. See research sections 6 and 9 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
{"schema_version":1,"event_id":"sase-5l:000011:issue_created:sase-5l.10","timestamp":"2026-07-08T05:13:57Z","actor":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","operation":"issue_created","issue_id":"sase-5l.10","payload":{"kind":"issue_created","issue":{"id":"sase-5l.10","title":"doctor: add resources.chezmoi and config.skills.applied deep checks","status":"open","issue_type":"phase","parent_id":"sase-5l","owner":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","assignee":"","created_at":"2026-07-08T05:13:57Z","created_by":"bryanbugyi34@gmail.com","updated_at":"2026-07-08T05:13:57Z","closed_at":null,"close_reason":null,"description":"Add two deep, conditional chezmoi checks. resources.chezmoi: SKIP unless use_chezmoi is true or the chezmoi source tree exists; ERROR when enabled but chezmoi is missing; WARN for suspicious source state. config.skills.applied: stat the real home skill targets and advise chezmoi apply when the chezmoi source and applied home state diverge (source can look current while applied copies are stale or missing). Add tests. See research section 9 and the epic plan design file.","notes":"","design":"","model":"","is_ready_to_work":false,"changespec_name":"","changespec_bug_id":"","dependencies":[]}}}
